cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it investigates the optimization of loss functions in deep neural networks. It also involves empirical analysis of state-of-the-art networks, which is a common theme in cs.LG. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The use of stochastic gradient descent variants also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The investigation of loss functions and optimization algorithms may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
